1
00:01:21,090 --> 00:01:24,940
A tension that had been brewing for
months in Nigeria exploded yesterday...

2
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:29,140
...as exiled Gen. Mustafa Yakubu
orchestrated a swift and violent coup...

3
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:33,490
...against the democratically elected
government of President Samuel Azuka.

4
00:01:33,650 --> 00:01:37,690
in the land with 120 million people
and over 250 ethnic groups...

5
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:40,530
... there'd been a long history
of ethnic enmity...

6
00:01:40,690 --> 00:01:45,020
...particularly between northern Fulani
Moslems and southern Christian lbo.

7
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:48,250
The victorious Fulani rebels
have taken to the streets...

8
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:51,900
...as outbursts of violence
continue all over the country.

9
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:56,890
Thousands have been killed in
the fighting or executed thereafter.

10
00:01:57,060 --> 00:02:00,700
Fearing ethnic cleansing, most lbo
have abandoned their homes...

11
00:02:00,850 --> 00:02:05,020
...and are fleeing the city or searching
for sanctuary wherever they may find it.

12
00:02:05,180 --> 00:02:08,260
Gen. Yakubu has taken control
of most of the country...

13
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:10,140
...and appears firmly in charge.

14
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:13,050
There's no word on the United Nations'
reaction to the coup...

15
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:17,050
...but United States forces have already
begun to evacuate its embassy.

16
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:37,460
As you can see behind me,
on the USS Harry S. Truman...

17
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:42,900
...activity is high as foreign nationals
are evacuated from all over Nigeria.

18
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,580
This once peaceful country...

19
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:49,130
...has been rocked by a series of ethnic
unrests and brief but bitter battles...

20
00:02:49,330 --> 00:02:52,410
...mainly over control
of Nigeria's vast oil supply.

21
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:54,860
However, nothing can prepare
the country...

22
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:59,300
...for the overwhelming and decisive
action that has just taken place.

23
00:03:02,010 --> 00:03:05,450
We have just heard
that the entire presidential family...

24
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,780
...has been assassinated.
l repeat:

25
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:11,420
The entire presidential family
has been assassinated.

26
00:03:28,170 --> 00:03:29,850
-Welcome aboard, Mr. Ambassador.
-Thank you.

27
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,450
Let me take those for you.

28
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,610
He got one in the leg!

29
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:36,580
Put him in the sickbay now!

30
00:03:40,610 --> 00:03:42,010
Well, look at you.

31
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,890
-Welcome back.
-Thank you.

32
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:48,900
We appreciate you've been humping out
there, but we have to put you back in.

33
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:53,820
Priority tasking. We need to extract
a critical personality ASAP.

34
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:57,210
Now get some chow,
refit for a three-day LLRP.

35
00:03:57,650 --> 00:04:00,250
See you in chow to debrief.
You...

36
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:02,940
-...go see the medic.
-Aye, captain.

37
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,020
Attention on deck.

38
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:15,660
As you were, gentlemen. Sit down.

39
00:04:20,780 --> 00:04:21,980
Everybody get chow?

40
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:24,220
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

41
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:28,370
Now, intel estimates
5000 Yakubu troops...

42
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:29,570
...scattered throughout this sector.

43
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,900
They've captured
government armories...

44
00:04:33,090 --> 00:04:37,010
...and unfortunately, we have been
supplying them for far too many years.

45
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:43,900
in addition, the local militia are killing
anyone who goes to a different church.

46
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:47,570
All right, now, your prime objective
is to find and extract...

47
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:52,210
...Dr. Lena Fiore Kendricks with
International Relief Services.

48
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:54,810
Dr. Kendricks is an American
by marriage.

49
00:04:55,090 --> 00:04:57,980
Her late husband
was Dr. John Kendricks.

50
00:04:58,130 --> 00:04:59,460
Your secondary objective...

51
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:02,940
...is to extract two nuns and a priest
who run a feel-good near Yolingo...

52
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:05,020
...if they so choose to leave.

53
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:07,420
St. Michael's Mission, right here.

54
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:09,330
You will halo over Cameroon...

55
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:12,810
...and float into your DZ near the edge
of the Mazon Rain Forest.

56
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,140
When you get your package...

57
00:05:14,290 --> 00:05:18,290
...you will proceed
to your extract LZ Alpha.

58
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:22,300
Our presence on the ground
will be considered hostile.

59
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:25,290
-Questions?
-Sir...

60
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:26,540
...rules of engagement?

61
00:05:26,690 --> 00:05:30,820
You will defend yourselves if you're
fired upon. Otherwise, do not engage.

62
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:32,860
Sir, what's our escape-and-evasion
plan?

63
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:36,380
Patrol the Cameroon border
through the Tandjile Pass.

64
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:39,090
Anything else, gentlemen?

65
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:42,780
All right.

66
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:44,860
Dismissed.

67
00:05:55,620 --> 00:05:57,330
Gentlemen, three minutes out.

68
00:07:31,490 --> 00:07:32,850
it’s okay. it’s okay.

69
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,410
You speak English?
You speak English?

70
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,970
Good. Good.
I’m not gonna hurt you.

71
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,970
Are there any soldiers here?
Any rebel soldiers?

72
00:07:42,140 --> 00:07:44,370
You sure? You sure?

73
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:47,540
Good. Good. Can you take me
to Dr. Lena Kendricks?

74
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,530
Do you know who she is?
Okay, here we go.

75
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:51,650
Nice and easy. Come on.

76
00:07:52,050 --> 00:07:53,660
Zee, we're moving.

77
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:56,530
it’s all right. I’m not gonna
hurt you, okay?

78
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:11,420
Open.

79
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:20,210
Clear.

80
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:45,820
Lasana, where's that wa...?

81
00:08:45,970 --> 00:08:47,980
These American men are here
to see you!

82
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:52,050
I’m Lt. Waters with the U.S. Navy.
I’m here to get you and your people out.

83
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:54,460
We're in the middle of surgery here.

84
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:56,780
Ma'am, you don't realize
what's about to happen here.

85
00:08:56,930 --> 00:08:58,700
Are you a nun?
Are you one of the nuns?

86
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,210
-Are you a nun, ma'am?
-Yes, sir.

87
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:03,290
Good. Pack your things
and let's get out of here now.

88
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:05,090
-Lieutenant!
-Ma'am.

89
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:08,850
Get those weapons out
of my operating room.

90
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,620
You're frightening my staff.

91
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:15,260
I’ll be with you when I’m done.
Now please wait outside!

92
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,250
Your staff should be frightened,
ma'am.

93
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:20,660
Do you know what'll happen to you
and these women when rebels get here?

94
00:09:25,730 --> 00:09:27,650
Doc, maybe you can help her out.

95
00:09:27,850 --> 00:09:29,820
Ma'am, may l assist?

96
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:32,530
-Are you a doctor?
-No, I’m a corpsman, ma'am.

97
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,700
-Can you stitch?
-Yes, ma'am.

98
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:36,860
-Are you sure?
-Yeah, he's sure.

99
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:41,210
Then close for me.

100
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:44,860
We're taking our good old time here.

101
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:52,210
All right, Lt. Waters, I’m all yours.

102
00:09:55,340 --> 00:09:56,370
Hurry up, Doc.

103
00:10:00,940 --> 00:10:03,580
l assume you have a plan
to get us all out of here?

104
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:05,570
Yes, ma'am. Come with me, please.

105
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:08,940
We've got a 1 2-klick hike to make
to rendezvous to the helicopter.

106
00:10:09,180 --> 00:10:11,260
Get your things together,
but pack light.

107
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:16,050
Zee, bring your perimeter up.
Keep Flea in place.

108
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,850
We spotted a rebel company
outside of Yolingo on the way in.

109
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:21,650
We must assume they'll be here
by night, if not sooner.

110
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:25,580
I’m responsible for 7 0 people here, more
than half of them seriously wounded.

111
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:28,450
My orders are to evacuate
foreign nationals only, ma'am.

112
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:30,130
What does that mean?

113
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,540
I mean non indigenous personnel,
ma'am.

114
00:10:32,690 --> 00:10:33,890
Then we have a problem.

115
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:38,460
l will not leave without
the indigenous personnel.

116
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:42,490
We're here to get you out.
Now, l suggest you go find the priest...

117
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:45,420
...go find the nuns, pack your things
and prepare to move.

118
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:49,810
When the rebel troops get here,
they'll kill everything they see...

119
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:51,890
...including privileged white doctors.

120
00:10:52,060 --> 00:10:55,100
-What part of that plan don't you get?
-The Cameroon border's 40 miles away!

121
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:58,300
-You could fly them out in 30 minutes!
-Can't do that.

122
00:10:58,450 --> 00:11:00,290
-Why not?
-Because my orders are very clear:

123
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:04,940
Evacuate the priest, you and the two
nuns. Now pack and get ready to move.

124
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,260
We can take those who can walk.

125
00:11:07,420 --> 00:11:10,130
They're not my responsibility.
You are my responsibility.

126
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,770
You're right, lieutenant...

127
00:11:19,010 --> 00:11:22,180
...it's not your problem.
it is my responsibility...

128
00:11:22,330 --> 00:11:25,020
...and l will not leave
without my people.

129
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:33,420
All right, give me a minute.

130
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:36,060
-A minute?
-That's right.

131
00:11:36,540 --> 00:11:40,850
Sixty seconds. l suggest you use
that time to go find the priest.

132
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:47,540
Get Command on the horn.

133
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:49,010
Eagle One to Command.

134
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:51,900
-Lena, what's going on?
-l don't know yet.

135
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:53,860
Eagle One to Command.

136
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:59,420
Eagle One.

137
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:01,980
Yeah, captain, we got a problem.

138
00:12:02,130 --> 00:12:03,180
No, we got her.

139
00:12:03,730 --> 00:12:06,940
But she wants to bring the 7 0 people
here along with her.

140
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,890
Yes, sir, l understand.

141
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:11,580
l will handle it.

142
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,170
Eagle One, out.

143
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:24,220
Dr. Kendricks.

144
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:33,900
You win. Get your people together.
We leave in a half an hour.

145
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:36,130
There will be helicopters for them too?

146
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:39,570
Yes. We can only take those who can
move under their own power.

147
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:42,130
l understand.

148
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:43,980
Thank you, lieutenant.

149
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:45,820
Hurry, please.

150
00:12:53,820 --> 00:12:56,690
Why don't we just get Doc
to tranq her the fuck out?

151
00:12:56,860 --> 00:13:00,300
That's a great idea, Red. Drugging
and kidnapping an American doctor.

152
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,420
I ain't sure this bitch is American.

153
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:06,290
The doctor is the mission, Red.
Stick with her.

154
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:10,690
-And we're taking all these people out?
-Go on.

155
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:15,780
We need everyone able
to travel ready to go.

156
00:13:15,930 --> 00:13:18,340
We must leave quickly.
Quickly!

157
00:13:18,490 --> 00:13:20,500
God will bless you, Lena.

158
00:13:27,660 --> 00:13:30,980
-What did the captain say?
-What the fuck you think he said?

159
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:40,250
Okay, let's clear these hooches.

160
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:52,540
Come here, you guys.

161
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:56,370
it’s okay. it’s okay. Come on.

162
00:14:58,890 --> 00:15:01,450
Hour and a half off the rendezvous
with the bird.

163
00:15:02,780 --> 00:15:05,620
-Can only bring what they carry by back.
-Roger that.

164
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:09,930
-Where's that priest?
-He says he ain't coming.

165
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:15,620
Bless you, Lena.

166
00:15:16,050 --> 00:15:17,370
Thank you for everything.

167
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:20,380
Don't cry, Sister, please.
We'll see each other again.

168
00:15:20,540 --> 00:15:22,090
Take care of yourself.

169
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:32,300
-You got it, Lake?
-Hundred percent, sir.

170
00:15:32,540 --> 00:15:33,570
All right. Let's go.

171
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:35,860
Take us out of here,
but don't run away from us.

172
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:37,620
Roger that.

173
00:15:41,660 --> 00:15:43,980
Keep them moving. Keep them moving.

174
00:15:44,130 --> 00:15:45,220
Come on.

175
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:49,690
Keep them moving, Slo.
Get her out of there.

176
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:52,700
Come on. Come on. Come on.
Hey. Come on, let's go.

177
00:15:52,860 --> 00:15:54,100
-Come on, now.
-Catch up!

178
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,900
Sister Grace.

179
00:15:56,050 --> 00:15:58,570
-The mother?
-She is dead.

180
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,380
Oh, no.

181
00:16:00,770 --> 00:16:02,370
Oh, no.

182
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:04,730
What am l going to do
with this child?

183
00:16:04,890 --> 00:16:06,060
Lena.

184
00:16:06,220 --> 00:16:10,290
Lena, you'll have to take this child.
it’s the only chance she has.

185
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:13,370
We gotta move quicker than this.

186
00:16:15,690 --> 00:16:18,460
We gotta get back for the Falcon game.
Come on.

187
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:20,580
Take care of yourself, girl.

188
00:16:27,610 --> 00:16:29,380
Sister Siobhan.

189
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,740
Mind yourself.

190
00:16:39,090 --> 00:16:42,170
Let's go, Sister. Pick your bag up.
Let's go now.

191
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:43,850
I’m not going.

192
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:45,380
Sister!

193
00:16:45,540 --> 00:16:47,740
-L.T., she doesn't want to leave.
-I’m not going.

194
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,060
What?

195
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,940
Good luck.

196
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,570
-God bless you.
-Thanks be to God.

197
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:01,220
All right, let's make it quick.

198
00:17:01,370 --> 00:17:03,100
Come on, ma'am, let's go.

199
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,730
Come on. We have plenty of work
to do now. Come on.

200
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:08,980
Take care.

201
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:19,580
Go with God.

202
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:25,100
-God already left Africa.
-Yeah.

203
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,860
Go easy, doc. Watch your step.

204
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:42,860
l got her.

205
00:18:56,370 --> 00:19:00,570
We're only five klicks in. it’s seven
and a half miles to LZ Alpha.

206
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:03,900
We go any slower, we'll start going
backwards in time.

207
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:06,850
-Red, what do you got back there?
-Five stragglers.

208
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:10,650
-30 meters and falling from main body.
-All right, roll them up ASAP.

209
00:19:11,730 --> 00:19:12,900
Let's go.

210
00:19:14,130 --> 00:19:16,210
Come on. You've gotta speed up.

211
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:19,490
Ma'am, speed up.
You too. You--

212
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:47,780
Watch those trees.

213
00:20:01,690 --> 00:20:03,330
I’m gonna help you.

214
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,700
it’s all right. I’ll tell them.

215
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,570
We got you.

216
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:23,010
Lieutenant.

217
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:25,490
We need to stop.

218
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:29,010
-Lieutenant!
-l heard you.

219
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:33,580
We can't stop.
Behind schedule. Come on.

220
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:35,980
These people need to rest.

221
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:38,340
And we have a child
who needs medication.

222
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:40,050
Here we go.

223
00:20:42,020 --> 00:20:44,580
There you go, ma'am.
Let's go.

224
00:20:46,090 --> 00:20:47,770
Let's go, doctor.

225
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:54,530
Come on, sir. Here we go.

226
00:20:57,810 --> 00:20:59,730
What you want to do?

227
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:03,490
Rest for 30.

228
00:21:03,650 --> 00:21:05,090
Lake, hold it up.

229
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:07,300
We're gonna rest for 30.

230
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:09,020
Set a perimeter.

231
00:21:11,060 --> 00:21:12,060
Perimeter up.

232
00:21:13,090 --> 00:21:16,060
Ma'am, we gonna take 30.

233
00:22:39,380 --> 00:22:42,860
L.T., we got guerrilla rebels inbound...

234
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:44,740
... on our path.

235
00:22:45,220 --> 00:22:48,370
Dr. Kendricks, come with me
right away. Come here.

236
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:53,290
There's danger on the trail. You must do
everything you can to-- Listen to me!

237
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:56,660
You must do everything you can to keep
that baby quiet, you understand me?

238
00:22:56,810 --> 00:22:59,090
Whatever it takes. Go now.

239
00:23:08,010 --> 00:23:09,620
Get up. Get up.

240
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:12,930
Danger close.

241
00:23:26,460 --> 00:23:28,020
Go.

242
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,690
Clear.

243
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:03,260
Oh, fuck. L.T., straggler, straggler.
Danger close.

244
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:40,940
Go on, ma'am. Go.
Now is good. Go!

245
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:44,370
Lake, lead us out before they
realize their tailgunner's gone.

246
00:26:45,050 --> 00:26:47,370
And find us a safe place to rest.

247
00:26:48,170 --> 00:26:51,060
Wait! They're going to the mission.
You have to stop them.

248
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:54,780
l can't do that. It'd risk the safety
of all these people here.

249
00:26:55,370 --> 00:26:58,780
-Besides, they may bypass the mission.
-You know they won't.

250
00:26:59,570 --> 00:27:02,780
There are a lot of possible scenarios
that could happen, Dr. Kendricks.

251
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:05,490
l don't presume
to know them all. Red?

252
00:27:06,060 --> 00:27:07,500
Dr. Kendricks.

253
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:09,340
-Let's go.
-Ma'am.

254
00:27:09,650 --> 00:27:10,810
Come on.

255
00:28:05,740 --> 00:28:08,340
Can't you sleep, lieutenant?

256
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,460
it’s my watch, ma'am.

257
00:28:11,420 --> 00:28:13,330
You can call me Lena.

258
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:18,420
Dr. Kendricks, l suggest
you get some rest.

259
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,140
You know....

260
00:28:29,620 --> 00:28:31,260
Thank you for saving my life.

261
00:28:35,810 --> 00:28:37,860
it wasn't about saving your life.

262
00:28:39,740 --> 00:28:41,980
it’s about getting the job done.

263
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:45,340
Completing the mission, that's all.

264
00:29:01,460 --> 00:29:02,940
My dear...

265
00:29:03,300 --> 00:29:08,130
...a thousand difficulties
don't make a doubt.

266
00:29:08,370 --> 00:29:13,330
-But I’m not a good Catholic.
-You don't know that. Only God knows.

267
00:29:16,570 --> 00:29:17,970
Gentlemen.

268
00:29:18,650 --> 00:29:19,890
Please.

269
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:23,420
This is a house of God.
We have no soldiers here.

270
00:29:23,570 --> 00:29:25,650
There are only sick people here.

271
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:28,530
Please, sir.

272
00:29:29,340 --> 00:29:31,700
-Gentlemen, please.
-No! No!

273
00:29:31,900 --> 00:29:33,580
No! Please! Please!

274
00:29:33,780 --> 00:29:35,770
-No!
-No!

275
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:40,010
Commander, please.
This is a house of God.

276
00:29:40,340 --> 00:29:44,410
We have no soldiers here. We have
hope. We have only sick people here.

277
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:46,490
We have only sick people here.

278
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:47,890
Please.

279
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:52,850
No, commander.

280
00:29:53,020 --> 00:29:55,650
And blessed is the fruit of thy womb,
Jesus.

281
00:29:55,820 --> 00:29:57,620
Holy Mary, mother of God...

282
00:29:57,860 --> 00:30:01,420
...pray for us sinners
now at the hour of our death.

283
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:02,690
Commander, no!

284
00:30:02,860 --> 00:30:04,660
-Blessed....
-No!

285
00:30:05,420 --> 00:30:07,980
Holy Mary, mother of God....

286
00:30:20,930 --> 00:30:22,810
What the fuck was that?

287
00:30:24,860 --> 00:30:25,940
Hyena.

288
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:31,820
Flea, Lake, status?

289
00:30:32,410 --> 00:30:33,810
Clear.

290
00:30:36,650 --> 00:30:37,660
Clear, L.T.

291
00:30:38,490 --> 00:30:39,970
Zee?

292
00:30:41,020 --> 00:30:43,890
Star One, this is Eagle One.
Be advised on location.

293
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:48,500
This is Star One. My ETA,
your location, five minutes.

294
00:30:48,660 --> 00:30:50,210
Popping smoke.

295
00:31:12,010 --> 00:31:13,580
Do you have smoke?

296
00:31:17,410 --> 00:31:18,620
Roger. Yellow smoke.

297
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:20,380
That's us.

298
00:31:30,620 --> 00:31:31,620
Eyes on.

299
00:32:03,220 --> 00:32:04,210
Slo, bring her up.

300
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:07,380
-Let's go! Come on! Now!
-Let's go, ma'am. Come on.

301
00:32:07,530 --> 00:32:10,290
Let's go now! Come on! You're first!
Let's go!

302
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:12,020
Goddamn it, let's go! We're late.

303
00:32:16,170 --> 00:32:17,180
Come on!

304
00:32:24,850 --> 00:32:27,340
Why doesn't the other helicopter
come down?!

305
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:29,900
it’s a gunship!
it’s here to protect us!

306
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:33,580
-What about the others?
-They'll be fine! Keep moving! Hurry up!

307
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:35,130
You gotta move faster!

308
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:37,140
-What are you doing?!
-Keep your head down!

309
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:38,300
Stand back.

310
00:32:38,460 --> 00:32:40,050
-Where is she going?
-Wait! Back!

311
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:43,140
Keep your head down!

312
00:32:43,810 --> 00:32:45,370
-Let us go!
-Dr. Lena!

313
00:32:45,580 --> 00:32:47,810
-Wait! Get back!
-Dr. Lena!

314
00:32:48,010 --> 00:32:51,820
Answer me! You never planned
on taking all of us out, did you?

315
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:56,140
l simply follow orders! My orders are
to get you out! Get on the helicopter!

316
00:32:56,300 --> 00:32:58,730
-What about my people?!
-I’m not here for them.

317
00:32:58,900 --> 00:32:59,970
You lied to me!

318
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:01,850
You lied to me!

319
00:33:02,050 --> 00:33:04,810
Liar! Bastard!

320
00:33:05,810 --> 00:33:08,220
Lena! Let me go!

321
00:33:08,370 --> 00:33:11,020
What about my people?!
l won't leave them!

322
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:12,940
You lied to me!

323
00:33:13,940 --> 00:33:15,940
-They're gonna die!
-Secure the doctor.

324
00:33:16,130 --> 00:33:18,690
Dr. Lena! Dr. Lena!

325
00:33:21,100 --> 00:33:22,780
Who decides for me?! You?!

326
00:33:23,420 --> 00:33:25,010
Your government?!

327
00:33:25,340 --> 00:33:28,140
Bastard! l won't leave them!

328
00:33:28,290 --> 00:33:30,610
Let's go! Let's go now!
Let's go!

329
00:33:38,130 --> 00:33:39,660
Let's go! Go! Let's go!

330
00:33:39,860 --> 00:33:42,900
Lena! Lena!

331
00:33:43,050 --> 00:33:44,060
Listen to me!

332
00:33:47,860 --> 00:33:50,340
Listen to me! it’s okay.

333
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:58,620
Let's go!

334
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:22,490
Lt. Waters. Starboard side.

335
00:35:23,250 --> 00:35:24,820
We saw this on the way in.

336
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:37,820
No!

337
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,610
No!

338
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:42,450
No!

339
00:35:54,540 --> 00:35:56,490
-Doc!
-No!

340
00:35:56,660 --> 00:35:57,650
Come on.

341
00:37:03,100 --> 00:37:05,330
Let's turn it around.

342
00:37:58,100 --> 00:37:59,300
Musa.

343
00:38:00,130 --> 00:38:01,180
Patience!

344
00:38:08,220 --> 00:38:10,020
Lena!

345
00:38:23,330 --> 00:38:25,340
We can only take 1 2 people.

346
00:38:25,500 --> 00:38:27,580
Old, young, anybody
who'll slow us down.

347
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:30,290
We'll meet up again in Cameroon.

348
00:38:33,700 --> 00:38:35,860
Go. And tell the others.

349
00:38:38,050 --> 00:38:40,850
-God will bless you.
-Hurry, please.

350
00:38:51,020 --> 00:38:52,380
Thank you.

351
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:12,540
Hurry, please.

352
00:39:17,570 --> 00:39:18,700
Red!

353
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:20,370
Go with the package.

354
00:39:21,020 --> 00:39:22,090
Now, goddamn it!

355
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:31,740
What are you doing?

356
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:37,140
New mission?

357
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:39,100
No.

358
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:40,500
Same mission.

359
00:39:41,970 --> 00:39:43,570
Get them ready, Zee.

360
00:39:53,260 --> 00:39:56,780
God will protect you.
Take Mama's cross. Take Mama's cross.

361
00:39:56,930 --> 00:39:58,530
Let's go! Get her ready.

362
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:01,340
We gotta go. We gotta go.

363
00:40:01,500 --> 00:40:03,660
Let's go! Let's go. Come on!

364
00:40:05,650 --> 00:40:07,380
Get her out of there!
Get off!

365
00:40:07,540 --> 00:40:09,900
-Patience! She'll be safe.
-She's my baby!

366
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:11,060
Keep your head down.

367
00:40:14,620 --> 00:40:16,610
She has no one to care for her.

368
00:40:21,090 --> 00:40:23,260
Ma'am, you gotta take this baby!

369
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:24,610
Hold her tight!

370
00:40:24,770 --> 00:40:27,700
-Keep your heads down!
-No more packs, sir. We're maxed out.

371
00:40:27,890 --> 00:40:29,490
See you in Cameroon.

372
00:40:29,730 --> 00:40:31,300
Come on. Let's go.

373
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:33,140
Here we go. Stay low.

374
00:40:34,060 --> 00:40:35,420
Head down.

375
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:38,500
Let's go.

376
00:40:38,650 --> 00:40:40,250
Sergeant! Let's go!

377
00:41:18,210 --> 00:41:20,050
Eagle One, over.

378
00:41:22,060 --> 00:41:23,700
Can you wait one, sir?

379
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:26,540
A.K.

380
00:41:26,850 --> 00:41:28,010
Command.

381
00:41:28,340 --> 00:41:29,340
Yes, sir?

382
00:41:29,500 --> 00:41:33,740
Lieutenant, why is that bird full of
refugees and not your criticals?

383
00:41:33,890 --> 00:41:35,730
The doctor wouldn't leave her people.

384
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:37,810
You can't get a woman on a helo?

385
00:41:37,980 --> 00:41:39,100
She was on the bird.

386
00:41:39,820 --> 00:41:42,260
-it’s difficult to explain, sir.
-Oh, come on.

387
00:41:42,420 --> 00:41:45,940
We're marching them to LZ Bravo.
Request helicopters to take them out.

388
00:41:46,090 --> 00:41:47,730
Negative on the evac at LZ Bravo.

389
00:41:47,890 --> 00:41:51,010
Come on, give me three choppers. I’ll
have them in Cameroon in 20 minutes.

390
00:41:51,170 --> 00:41:52,330
Negative!

391
00:41:52,500 --> 00:41:55,100
Birds have taken heavy fire. We've
stopped entering Nigerian airspace.

392
00:41:55,260 --> 00:41:58,140
We'll give you what help we can
from our end, but right now...

393
00:41:58,300 --> 00:41:59,540
...you are on your own.

394
00:42:02,410 --> 00:42:04,180
Man, l hope you know
what you're doing.

395
00:42:05,210 --> 00:42:06,340
Me too, sir.

396
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:09,380
All right. We'll keep you advised
if the situation changes.

397
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:13,490
Negative on the evac.

398
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:18,740
Come on. There you go. Come on.

399
00:42:19,860 --> 00:42:21,650
Hang on to the knot, doctor.

400
00:42:22,130 --> 00:42:23,180
-Come on.
-We got you.

401
00:42:23,330 --> 00:42:25,130
Come on. Come on, doc.

402
00:42:57,250 --> 00:42:58,780
Americans.

403
00:43:00,460 --> 00:43:02,570
Some went in the helicopter.

404
00:43:04,530 --> 00:43:06,610
Some went up the mountain...

405
00:43:07,330 --> 00:43:08,540
...to Cameroon.

406
00:44:12,890 --> 00:44:14,010
Slo.

407
00:44:21,420 --> 00:44:22,930
Give me your chow, man.

408
00:44:26,930 --> 00:44:28,970
l don't like roast beef anyway.

409
00:44:39,460 --> 00:44:42,420
We're a little over 30 klicks
to the path to Cameroon.

410
00:44:42,570 --> 00:44:43,700
Roger that.

411
00:44:53,660 --> 00:44:54,730
What do you got?

412
00:44:55,540 --> 00:44:59,860
We got a large body 1 0 klicks back,
bearing 3-6-0 and closing.

413
00:45:00,170 --> 00:45:01,330
How strong?

414
00:45:01,500 --> 00:45:04,330
Thirty, maybe platoon strength,
maybe more.

415
00:45:04,850 --> 00:45:06,010
Rebels?

416
00:45:07,060 --> 00:45:08,260
Could be.

417
00:45:08,850 --> 00:45:11,100
Why would anybody be following us?

418
00:45:12,090 --> 00:45:13,290
l don't know.

419
00:45:15,410 --> 00:45:17,010
But we're gonna find out.

420
00:45:18,100 --> 00:45:19,220
Good job.

421
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:21,540
-Keep an eye on them.
-Roger that.

422
00:45:23,130 --> 00:45:24,730
-Sir?
-We got a problem.

423
00:45:24,900 --> 00:45:27,290
We got possible hostiles on our 6.

424
00:45:27,460 --> 00:45:29,210
Get them up, get them ready to move.

425
00:45:29,370 --> 00:45:30,780
Roger that.

426
00:45:33,580 --> 00:45:36,540
Dr. Kendricks, could you come with me,
please?

427
00:45:36,690 --> 00:45:39,050
Thank you. it’ll just take a second.

428
00:45:43,380 --> 00:45:46,860
-Do you know why anybody'd follow us?
-No, l don't.

429
00:45:47,060 --> 00:45:48,260
You sure?

430
00:45:49,740 --> 00:45:50,970
Yes, I’m sure.

431
00:45:59,980 --> 00:46:03,260
-Think hard.
-l told you, l don't know.

432
00:46:04,940 --> 00:46:06,300
Get your people ready to go now.

433
00:46:06,580 --> 00:46:09,340
These people have been going
for over 30 hours.

434
00:46:09,930 --> 00:46:11,260
Come on.

435
00:46:13,010 --> 00:46:15,570
Red, help the doctor get ready to move.

436
00:47:19,380 --> 00:47:20,980
How you doing?

437
00:47:22,290 --> 00:47:24,220
The fuck you mean, how am l doing?

438
00:47:24,370 --> 00:47:26,140
You know what I’m talking about.

439
00:47:36,420 --> 00:47:37,970
You know as well as l do...

440
00:47:38,140 --> 00:47:40,970
...that when we left that mission,
those people were dead.

441
00:47:42,300 --> 00:47:45,820
And then we take 28 men, women
and children...

442
00:47:46,370 --> 00:47:48,220
...and we hump for a day.

443
00:47:48,420 --> 00:47:50,650
Zee, keep them moving.

444
00:47:50,890 --> 00:47:52,900
Be with you in a second.

445
00:47:53,820 --> 00:47:57,740
We get them to the LZ, and we leave
them behind to die like the others.

446
00:47:58,420 --> 00:47:59,900
I’m confused.

447
00:48:00,060 --> 00:48:01,780
And the boys are confused.

448
00:48:01,980 --> 00:48:03,380
Get to the point.

449
00:48:03,930 --> 00:48:06,570
Why'd you turn that bird around, L.T.?

450
00:48:08,060 --> 00:48:09,420
Talk to me.

451
00:48:10,340 --> 00:48:13,220
I’m with you either way.
You know that.

452
00:48:15,780 --> 00:48:17,970
When l figure it out, I’ll let you know.

453
00:48:30,610 --> 00:48:32,220
This way.

454
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:18,100
-L.T.
-Go, Lake.

455
00:49:18,340 --> 00:49:21,140
You're gonna want to come
take a look at this.

456
00:49:26,780 --> 00:49:29,580
Get Dr. Kendricks up here. Come here.

457
00:49:30,420 --> 00:49:34,090
We'll rest here for a minute. Stay down
in these trees. Listen to my men. Go!

458
00:49:34,260 --> 00:49:35,250
Slo.

459
00:49:36,060 --> 00:49:37,330
Stay down. Stay down.

460
00:49:37,500 --> 00:49:39,660
Zee, Flea, with me.

461
00:49:44,170 --> 00:49:45,850
What do you got?

462
00:49:46,010 --> 00:49:49,020
Ringside seats to an ethnic cleansing.

463
00:50:01,690 --> 00:50:02,930
How strong?

464
00:50:03,130 --> 00:50:04,900
l counted seven so far, sir.

465
00:50:05,140 --> 00:50:07,020
-Flea, get eyes on.
-Roger that.

466
00:50:12,050 --> 00:50:14,610
There could be more in the hooches.

467
00:50:15,420 --> 00:50:16,730
Bring them up.

468
00:50:25,940 --> 00:50:28,650
Sir, we could go around them
to the north.

469
00:50:40,260 --> 00:50:41,700
L.T.

470
00:50:42,490 --> 00:50:44,500
Rules of engagement.

471
00:50:44,660 --> 00:50:46,580
We're already engaged.

472
00:50:50,650 --> 00:50:52,620
Hand me the binoculars.

473
00:50:57,690 --> 00:50:58,940
Flea, you got the Zippo?

474
00:51:00,210 --> 00:51:01,210
Roger that.

475
00:51:01,850 --> 00:51:03,420
Zippo first.

476
00:51:03,770 --> 00:51:08,100
Red Team, right flank. This way.
Edge of clearing. Wait for my go.

477
00:51:08,410 --> 00:51:11,180
Silent and quick.
Gold Team, on me.

478
00:51:14,330 --> 00:51:16,930
Silk, close up that back door.

479
00:51:17,330 --> 00:51:20,340
-Flea, keep your eye on the package.
-Roger that.

480
00:51:20,500 --> 00:51:21,940
Holding.

481
00:51:22,290 --> 00:51:23,410
Let's go.

482
00:51:31,540 --> 00:51:32,530
On-site.

483
00:52:24,420 --> 00:52:26,340
Goddamn.

484
00:52:30,850 --> 00:52:32,380
Been going at it all day.

485
00:52:48,140 --> 00:52:49,890
-On-site.
-Roger that.

486
00:53:24,050 --> 00:53:25,060
Go!

487
00:54:50,610 --> 00:54:52,730
it’s okay. I’m here to help you.

488
00:54:55,460 --> 00:54:57,010
I’ll help you. it’s okay.

489
00:54:58,020 --> 00:54:59,180
Atkins!

490
00:55:05,690 --> 00:55:06,770
Hide!

491
00:56:22,980 --> 00:56:24,530
Go! Run! Get out of here!

492
00:56:24,700 --> 00:56:26,340
-Doc, get them out of here!
-Move!

493
00:56:27,220 --> 00:56:28,220
Go! Go!

494
00:56:55,780 --> 00:56:58,140
Hold on. You hold on.

495
00:57:03,130 --> 00:57:04,850
Come on, little man, come on.

496
00:57:24,820 --> 00:57:27,620
Boss, you want me to take a look
at that?

497
00:57:29,370 --> 00:57:31,010
I’m all right.

498
00:58:06,300 --> 00:58:09,690
it’s a kid. it’s only a fucking kid.

499
00:58:22,330 --> 00:58:25,260
Motherfucker. Get the fuck up.

500
00:58:30,290 --> 00:58:32,100
Look at your work, motherfucker.

501
00:58:49,730 --> 00:58:51,090
Lake.

502
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:21,500
Doc, get over here.

503
00:59:36,530 --> 00:59:37,860
Red.

504
00:59:51,770 --> 00:59:53,780
Her baby's dead.

505
01:00:06,580 --> 01:00:08,170
Zee.

506
01:00:27,130 --> 01:00:30,650
Eternal rest grant unto her, oh, Lord.
Let perpetual light shine on her.

507
01:00:30,890 --> 01:00:34,020
May her soul and the souls
of all the dead rest in peace.

508
01:00:36,010 --> 01:00:39,330
Eternal rest grant unto her, oh, Lord.
Let perpetual light shine on her.

509
01:00:39,530 --> 01:00:42,420
May her soul and the souls
of all the dead rest in peace.

510
01:00:52,260 --> 01:00:53,850
She has a low pulse.

511
01:01:03,500 --> 01:01:05,580
How can they do this?

512
01:01:06,730 --> 01:01:08,740
This is what they do.

513
01:01:10,100 --> 01:01:13,050
They cut off the breasts
of nursing mothers...

514
01:01:13,290 --> 01:01:16,820
...so that they'll never again
feed their own babies.

515
01:01:19,370 --> 01:01:21,540
This is what they do.

516
01:01:27,250 --> 01:01:28,490
Doc.

517
01:01:30,090 --> 01:01:31,860
l need morphine.

518
01:03:51,220 --> 01:03:52,490
Dr. Kendricks.

519
01:03:55,450 --> 01:03:57,060
Dr. Kendricks.

520
01:04:01,700 --> 01:04:02,770
it’s all right.

521
01:05:05,930 --> 01:05:09,250
-Is something wrong?
-Let me take care of your arm.

522
01:05:11,850 --> 01:05:13,010
All right.

523
01:05:28,170 --> 01:05:29,300
Careful.

524
01:05:33,500 --> 01:05:35,010
Try this.

525
01:05:35,210 --> 01:05:37,300
it will help you stay awake.

526
01:05:39,180 --> 01:05:40,780
What is it?

527
01:05:40,940 --> 01:05:42,450
Cola nut from the tree.

528
01:05:46,860 --> 01:05:48,260
it’s harmless.

529
01:05:48,420 --> 01:05:50,300
We've been using them
for generations.

530
01:05:51,170 --> 01:05:53,340
Patience, right?

531
01:05:55,850 --> 01:05:57,450
How long you been at the mission?

532
01:05:58,580 --> 01:05:59,940
l live there.

533
01:06:00,090 --> 01:06:02,780
I’ve been living there since l was 1 0.

534
01:06:04,010 --> 01:06:05,100
How come?

535
01:06:05,860 --> 01:06:09,780
l heard they were helping children
who had been forced into the war...

536
01:06:10,410 --> 01:06:11,940
...so l ran to them.

537
01:06:17,850 --> 01:06:20,170
Will you get me to my daughter?

538
01:06:27,450 --> 01:06:28,810
Yes, ma'am.

539
01:06:38,100 --> 01:06:40,900
How'd you end up here in Africa?

540
01:06:41,220 --> 01:06:43,500
l came here with my husband.

541
01:06:45,140 --> 01:06:47,170
We wanted to help.

542
01:06:48,330 --> 01:06:52,380
We went to Sierra Leone.
They were short of doctors there.

543
01:06:52,970 --> 01:06:54,130
Cut.

544
01:07:02,130 --> 01:07:04,410
How did your husband die?

545
01:07:11,420 --> 01:07:13,980
We were at the hospital.

546
01:07:15,410 --> 01:07:17,220
The rebels came.

547
01:07:18,180 --> 01:07:22,530
My husband tried to stop them,
to protect me...

548
01:07:23,930 --> 01:07:25,620
...but he couldn't.

549
01:07:27,850 --> 01:07:29,340
I’m sorry.

550
01:07:38,060 --> 01:07:40,180
You did a good thing today.

551
01:07:48,420 --> 01:07:50,850
l don't know if it was a good thing
or not.

552
01:07:56,300 --> 01:07:58,900
Feels like so long since I’ve done...

553
01:08:00,170 --> 01:08:02,530
...a good thing, the right thing.

554
01:08:05,460 --> 01:08:07,690
You should have some rest.

555
01:08:09,860 --> 01:08:12,700
Thank you for taking care of my arm.

556
01:08:50,050 --> 01:08:51,540
Easy, boss.

557
01:09:02,970 --> 01:09:06,210
-Are we there yet?
-Glad to see you still got it...

558
01:09:06,580 --> 01:09:08,020
...but we got trouble.

559
01:09:13,380 --> 01:09:14,580
You all right?

560
01:09:17,300 --> 01:09:18,300
What do you got?

561
01:09:18,500 --> 01:09:21,140
This is the outfit
that's been on our tail.

562
01:09:21,610 --> 01:09:24,380
-Hey. You with me, boss?
-Yeah.

563
01:09:25,500 --> 01:09:28,100
-This is at 2200 hours.
-Yeah.

564
01:09:28,650 --> 01:09:30,420
Four hours ago.

565
01:09:30,660 --> 01:09:32,060
Three hours.

566
01:09:32,300 --> 01:09:35,690
We figured they'd make camp
and come at us after first light, right?

567
01:09:35,860 --> 01:09:37,220
Bad call.

568
01:09:37,460 --> 01:09:39,140
Two hours ago.

569
01:09:39,340 --> 01:09:40,340
One.

570
01:09:40,540 --> 01:09:45,140
These guys run the damned Olympics.
They've been closing in on us all night.

571
01:09:45,770 --> 01:09:47,540
How long we got?

572
01:09:48,500 --> 01:09:50,730
An hour, two tops.

573
01:09:51,210 --> 01:09:52,570
We shouldn't have stopped.

574
01:09:53,450 --> 01:09:55,780
How the fuck are they tracking us
at night?

575
01:10:02,540 --> 01:10:04,250
Someone's transmitting something.

576
01:10:10,740 --> 01:10:12,180
Zee.

577
01:10:13,820 --> 01:10:16,210
We got a rat in the nest.
Get them up.

578
01:10:16,380 --> 01:10:19,380
Take their weapons away.
We search everybody right now.

579
01:10:19,860 --> 01:10:21,330
-Okay, team.
-Dr. Kendricks.

580
01:10:21,500 --> 01:10:23,100
-Turn two.
-Lena. Get up.

581
01:10:23,250 --> 01:10:24,500
Everybody, up.

582
01:10:24,650 --> 01:10:27,860
Point out everybody that came into
the mission in the last three days.

583
01:10:28,020 --> 01:10:29,460
-Right now.
-Let's see the weapons.

584
01:10:31,620 --> 01:10:33,620
Give me your weapons.

585
01:10:37,860 --> 01:10:40,740
-Gideon.
-Let's go. Step forward, sir.

586
01:10:40,900 --> 01:10:42,300
Who else?

587
01:10:44,570 --> 01:10:45,970
Who else?!

588
01:10:46,260 --> 01:10:47,370
These people.

589
01:10:47,570 --> 01:10:50,580
-Step forward, you two, right now.
-On your knees.

590
01:10:50,740 --> 01:10:52,220
L.T.!

591
01:10:55,050 --> 01:10:56,340
Down! Now!

592
01:10:57,020 --> 01:10:58,170
Silk.

593
01:10:59,460 --> 01:11:01,130
No!

594
01:11:04,210 --> 01:11:07,140
-Hey! What the hell are you doing?
-He's my friend!

595
01:11:07,290 --> 01:11:09,130
You know what?
He could also be armed.

596
01:11:09,300 --> 01:11:11,820
Get back there with the others!
Go on!

597
01:11:16,890 --> 01:11:19,340
-Watch his hands.
-Fuck.

598
01:11:21,020 --> 01:11:22,250
Shit.

599
01:11:23,780 --> 01:11:25,770
What the hell is that?

600
01:11:26,490 --> 01:11:28,130
What do you got?

601
01:11:28,660 --> 01:11:29,860
He's bugged.

602
01:11:30,010 --> 01:11:31,460
You fuck!

603
01:11:37,010 --> 01:11:38,740
-Stop it!
-Who told you to do this?

604
01:11:38,890 --> 01:11:41,140
-They have my family.
-Who told you to do it?!

605
01:11:41,300 --> 01:11:43,700
-They have my family.
-Who has your family?!

606
01:11:43,860 --> 01:11:46,570
l was promised no harm
will come to them.

607
01:11:47,700 --> 01:11:49,650
-Who told you to do it?!
-Stop it!

608
01:11:50,290 --> 01:11:53,300
-Who told you to do it?!
-Col. Sadick.

609
01:11:54,020 --> 01:11:55,050
Col. Sadick.

610
01:11:56,500 --> 01:11:59,050
l am one of many
who give him information.

611
01:12:00,500 --> 01:12:02,490
About who?
Information about who?!

612
01:12:02,660 --> 01:12:04,500
We have to follow....

613
01:12:05,810 --> 01:12:07,540
Who?! Who?!

614
01:12:07,690 --> 01:12:09,940
We have to follow....

615
01:12:10,420 --> 01:12:12,570
-Follow who?!
-Arthur.

616
01:12:12,740 --> 01:12:14,170
Arthur?

617
01:12:21,860 --> 01:12:23,610
l am not a killer.

618
01:12:26,820 --> 01:12:28,490
The fuck you're not.

619
01:12:33,610 --> 01:12:36,490
-What do you wanna do with him?
-Let him bleed out.

620
01:12:41,060 --> 01:12:42,260
Why?

621
01:12:44,650 --> 01:12:49,370
What is going to happen
to my family?

622
01:12:51,380 --> 01:12:52,650
l don't know.

623
01:12:53,290 --> 01:12:55,930
-Help them.
-Zee. Lake.

624
01:12:56,330 --> 01:12:58,580
-Get them up.
-Everybody up. Now.

625
01:13:07,610 --> 01:13:09,730
Who knows what this is?

626
01:13:15,460 --> 01:13:17,140
This is a transmitter.

627
01:13:19,220 --> 01:13:22,260
l took this off Gideon's dead body...

628
01:13:23,050 --> 01:13:24,650
...Dr. Kendricks' good friend.

629
01:13:28,340 --> 01:13:30,220
You have any more of these here?

630
01:13:32,650 --> 01:13:35,300
Why would anybody wanna transmit
our position?

631
01:13:35,450 --> 01:13:39,860
Transmit our position
to over 300 Nigerian soldiers...

632
01:13:40,410 --> 01:13:41,700
...who ran all night...

633
01:13:42,580 --> 01:13:45,460
...to get to within an hour and a half
of where we are now?

634
01:13:50,860 --> 01:13:51,850
Red.

635
01:13:56,660 --> 01:13:59,020
Somebody's gonna tell me.

636
01:13:59,180 --> 01:14:01,690
Somebody's gonna start talking
right now.

637
01:14:02,810 --> 01:14:06,090
Because if they don't tell me
what l want to know...

638
01:14:06,260 --> 01:14:08,420
...by the time l count to five...

639
01:14:08,580 --> 01:14:10,740
...I’m gonna kill someone else.

640
01:14:11,620 --> 01:14:13,060
One.

641
01:14:15,140 --> 01:14:16,740
Two.

642
01:14:18,810 --> 01:14:20,610
Three.

643
01:14:22,290 --> 01:14:23,820
Don't fuck with me.

644
01:14:24,260 --> 01:14:26,340
-Four.
-Please.

645
01:14:27,060 --> 01:14:28,410
Please.

646
01:14:28,650 --> 01:14:30,100
There's no need for this.

647
01:14:32,410 --> 01:14:33,940
Please.

648
01:14:34,100 --> 01:14:36,660
Now you got something
to say to me, don't you?

649
01:14:37,140 --> 01:14:39,220
My name is Arthur Azuka.

650
01:14:41,930 --> 01:14:45,380
I’m the only son
of President Samuel Azuka.

651
01:14:48,860 --> 01:14:50,650
Please don't blame them.

652
01:14:51,610 --> 01:14:52,660
Please.

653
01:14:54,170 --> 01:14:56,010
I’m sorry to have misled you...

654
01:14:56,180 --> 01:14:58,810
...but there are enemies
looking for me everywhere.

655
01:14:59,050 --> 01:15:01,650
That is why you're being pursued.

656
01:15:04,650 --> 01:15:07,530
Our report said the entire
presidential family was executed.

657
01:15:07,900 --> 01:15:10,490
Your reports were incorrect.

658
01:15:11,450 --> 01:15:13,460
They were not executed.

659
01:15:13,940 --> 01:15:16,020
They murdered my father...

660
01:15:16,570 --> 01:15:18,580
...along with my mother...

661
01:15:19,450 --> 01:15:20,900
...and my two...

662
01:15:22,340 --> 01:15:23,780
...younger sisters...

663
01:15:25,380 --> 01:15:27,370
...out of greed...

664
01:15:28,090 --> 01:15:31,500
...and my father's fight for democracy
for his people.

665
01:15:34,890 --> 01:15:36,420
My people.

666
01:15:37,930 --> 01:15:40,420
When it first appeared
there might be trouble...

667
01:15:40,580 --> 01:15:43,050
...my father sent me away with this man.

668
01:15:44,420 --> 01:15:45,930
Col. Okeze.

669
01:15:47,770 --> 01:15:51,290
Lieutenant, his father was more
than the president.

670
01:15:51,450 --> 01:15:53,060
He was the tribal king.

671
01:15:53,220 --> 01:15:55,340
That makes him the heir
to the lbo nation.

672
01:15:55,930 --> 01:15:57,810
it’s a bloodline they must cut.

673
01:15:58,250 --> 01:16:01,770
The Fulanis will comb heaven
and earth to find him.

674
01:16:09,620 --> 01:16:11,060
You knew about this?

675
01:16:12,900 --> 01:16:15,370
You knew all the time,
and you didn't tell me.

676
01:16:18,260 --> 01:16:20,020
l didn't trust you...

677
01:16:20,250 --> 01:16:21,890
...at the time.

678
01:16:29,740 --> 01:16:31,810
l wonder what it takes
to earn your trust.

679
01:16:34,810 --> 01:16:36,380
Red, Lake.

680
01:16:41,500 --> 01:16:44,140
Tell them to pack their things.
We're leaving.

681
01:16:45,610 --> 01:16:48,450
Men, give them their weapons.
We're moving out of here.

682
01:16:48,610 --> 01:16:50,100
-Pack up your things.
-Come on.

683
01:16:50,250 --> 01:16:51,410
Move it out!

684
01:16:52,170 --> 01:16:54,290
-Get in, get out. Okay?
-Come on.

685
01:16:54,730 --> 01:16:56,500
Move it. Move it.

686
01:16:56,940 --> 01:16:59,740
-Come on. See you. Hurry back.
-Back in formation.

687
01:17:28,540 --> 01:17:32,340
They must continue their route to
the Tandjile Pass or they'll lose a day.

688
01:17:32,500 --> 01:17:36,650
So they must come out here,
near the Cameroon border.

689
01:17:39,860 --> 01:17:40,980
No!

690
01:18:10,090 --> 01:18:11,900
How many men
do you have in Gashanka?

691
01:18:19,050 --> 01:18:20,500
Right on time.

692
01:18:20,780 --> 01:18:23,340
Good hustle, Red.
Come on up and brief Zee.

693
01:18:26,250 --> 01:18:28,610
This river will get us
straight into Cameroon.

694
01:18:28,980 --> 01:18:30,620
They'll be expecting us.

695
01:18:32,130 --> 01:18:33,770
What do you think?

696
01:18:33,940 --> 01:18:36,130
l think we're fucked
either way we go.

697
01:18:37,580 --> 01:18:40,530
We backtrack, cross downstream...

698
01:18:40,700 --> 01:18:44,020
...come up, go through the jungle
and rip right into Cameroon.

699
01:18:45,420 --> 01:18:47,810
Roger that. Let the other men know.

700
01:18:47,980 --> 01:18:49,730
-Yes, sir.
-Good job.

701
01:18:50,570 --> 01:18:51,860
L.T.

702
01:18:52,450 --> 01:18:55,020
-What do you got?
-Rhodes on the phone.

703
01:18:58,530 --> 01:18:59,970
Yes, sir, captain, this is Waters.

704
01:19:00,140 --> 01:19:02,420
Intel reports military elements
in your sector...

705
01:19:02,570 --> 01:19:05,500
...conducting search and destroy
of a U.S. military unit...

706
01:19:05,940 --> 01:19:09,610
...moving with Arthur Azuka, son of the
late president. What can you tell me?

707
01:19:09,770 --> 01:19:12,020
Yes, sir, we just discovered that
ourselves.

708
01:19:12,170 --> 01:19:15,380
He and his bodyguard hid themselves
within Dr. Kendricks' refugee party.

709
01:19:16,780 --> 01:19:18,530
That's a major problem, lieutenant.

710
01:19:18,690 --> 01:19:22,380
He involves your mission in the
internal politics of a foreign nation...

711
01:19:22,540 --> 01:19:26,380
...affecting U.S. diplomacy and
seriously increases the mission's risk.

712
01:19:26,580 --> 01:19:29,100
He's considered a criminal
by the new regime.

713
01:19:29,290 --> 01:19:30,850
He's a major liability.

714
01:19:31,020 --> 01:19:34,370
-What exactly does that mean, sir?
-His party is excess cargo.

715
01:19:34,740 --> 01:19:36,340
You mean he's not human, sir?

716
01:19:36,970 --> 01:19:40,420
Captain, this man is the lbo tribal
leader. Do you know what that means?

717
01:19:40,580 --> 01:19:42,610
Cut the shit. Who do you think l am?

718
01:19:44,660 --> 01:19:47,770
Sir, we both know what'll happen to him
if l leave him out here.

719
01:19:47,970 --> 01:19:50,130
There won't be a trial or a jury.

720
01:19:50,290 --> 01:19:52,650
Outside the courthouse,
they'll put two in his head.

721
01:19:53,020 --> 01:19:56,410
I’m just asking for a little help here.
Put yourself in my shoes, Bill.

722
01:19:56,580 --> 01:19:58,180
I’ve been in your shoes, lieutenant.

723
01:19:58,330 --> 01:20:01,290
Send in an air evac immediately
and get all of us out of here, sir.

724
01:20:01,460 --> 01:20:04,780
Negative on air support at this time.
Airspace is too hot.

725
01:20:04,940 --> 01:20:09,180
Your judgment has risked the lives of
your men and the mission's success.

726
01:20:09,330 --> 01:20:12,500
l advise you, complete the evacuation
as planned! Do you read me?!

727
01:20:13,930 --> 01:20:16,020
Yes, sir, l read you. Loud and clear.

728
01:20:16,810 --> 01:20:20,330
But l cannot, in good conscience, do that
without taking these people to safety.

729
01:20:20,490 --> 01:20:21,540
That's not your mission!

730
01:20:21,690 --> 01:20:23,850
When have l not completed a mission?

731
01:20:25,250 --> 01:20:27,330
My team will complete this mission.

732
01:20:27,620 --> 01:20:29,010
l give you my word on that.

733
01:20:29,170 --> 01:20:30,810
l don't like this.

734
01:20:31,460 --> 01:20:33,610
Get your ass back here alive
soon as possible.

735
01:20:33,780 --> 01:20:35,770
Maintain contact with OP center.

736
01:20:38,020 --> 01:20:40,170
I’ll direct air support
as soon as l can.

737
01:20:40,500 --> 01:20:41,780
l promise you.

738
01:20:42,490 --> 01:20:43,620
Yes, sir.

739
01:20:44,540 --> 01:20:45,850
Eagle One, out.

740
01:20:48,580 --> 01:20:49,860
Bring them up.

741
01:20:50,490 --> 01:20:53,050
Everybody up on L.T. now. Double time.

742
01:20:53,290 --> 01:20:54,780
So much for diplomacy.

743
01:20:55,850 --> 01:20:57,180
Come on, let's go.

744
01:21:02,010 --> 01:21:05,770
Here's the deal. it’s been strongly
suggested that we turn over Arthur...

745
01:21:06,820 --> 01:21:09,450
...and abandon these refugees
out here in the bush.

746
01:21:11,530 --> 01:21:14,500
I’ll tell you right now
I’m not gonna do that.

747
01:21:15,020 --> 01:21:16,690
l can't do that.

748
01:21:18,740 --> 01:21:20,450
l broke my own rule.

749
01:21:21,780 --> 01:21:23,860
l started to give a fuck...

750
01:21:24,650 --> 01:21:27,210
...and brought you guys along with me.

751
01:21:28,340 --> 01:21:33,610
We're about to walk into some serious
shit. Before we do, I’d just like...

752
01:21:35,970 --> 01:21:39,930
...to hear what you guys have to say
about it. That's all. Speak freely.

753
01:21:40,980 --> 01:21:43,060
in my opinion, sir...

754
01:21:43,210 --> 01:21:46,300
...we cut our losses.
This isn't our fucking war.

755
01:21:47,650 --> 01:21:49,730
As far as me being in or out...

756
01:21:50,740 --> 01:21:52,330
...you know the answer to that.

757
01:21:55,020 --> 01:21:57,100
Let's get these people to safety.

758
01:21:58,060 --> 01:21:59,850
Let's finish the job.

759
01:22:02,740 --> 01:22:04,620
l can't leave them, sir.

760
01:22:07,220 --> 01:22:08,820
I’m good to go.

761
01:22:10,810 --> 01:22:12,780
What about you, Red?

762
01:22:17,090 --> 01:22:20,100
l can't look at them
like packages anymore.

763
01:22:21,810 --> 01:22:24,220
I’m gonna get them out...

764
01:22:24,740 --> 01:22:26,930
...or I’m going to die trying.

765
01:22:32,810 --> 01:22:34,580
Are we there yet?

766
01:22:40,620 --> 01:22:41,780
Thanks, fellas.

767
01:22:45,300 --> 01:22:47,940
Strip those packs down
to rolling gear only.

768
01:22:48,250 --> 01:22:52,180
Have the refugees drop anything
that don't go '' boom.'' Let's move.

769
01:22:54,410 --> 01:22:56,930
Double time. Let's go. Hustle.

